    <stitle>DT 466 / DT 570 / HT 570 Service Manual - 2004 Emissions with EGR - Flywheel and Flywheel Housing -
        Inspection - Removing Flywheel Housing
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc graphiccount="1">
        <title>Removing Flywheel Housing</title>
        <specpara>
            <warning>
                <para>To avoid serious personal injury, possible death, or damage to the engine or vehicle, do not
                    remove any engine mounting hardware until the engine is properly supported.
                </para>
            </warning>
        </specpara>
        <figure id="f2651319" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figH06/H06005.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Removing flywheel housing mounting bolts</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the eight mounting bolts that secure the flywheel housing to the crankcase.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use an assistant to help remove the flywheel housing from the engine.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Inspect for cracks.</para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
